When clicking on a plug-in on the UPM admin page, it seems hang with the spinning icon, and eventually the following error shows up:

{noformat}
An unexpected error occurred. Please refer to the logs for more information.
{noformat}

On the {{UPM}} admin page, at the bottom of the page, there are following error messages:
{noformat}
Error occurred during template rendering: Invocation of method 'getHtml' in class com.atlassian.plugin.web.descriptors.DefaultWebPanelModuleDescriptor$ContextAwareWebPanel threw exception java.lang.NullPointerException at template/includes/macros.vm[line 1908, column 20]. Contact your administrator for assistance.
{noformat}

I'm not sure the best way to update the docs, but they should indicate to the user the correct way to get to the Drafts page.

Something like:
{quote}To access your drafts, you'll need to go to the Browse menu in Confluence (the wiki tab) and select User Settings. Then you'll need to click the Drafts tab on the inner page that shows up.{quote}
